        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 4:51PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 451 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bardwell, or 10 miles south of Ennis, moving north at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of central Ellis and
northwestern Navarro Counties, including the following locations...
Avalon, Emhouse, and Howard.

This includes Interstate 45 between mile markers 246 and 251.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
